<br>
I am imagine a new plane, it is hard place, tough mobs, but has by far the best item of any other zone.<br>
<br>
There is one catch.<br>
<br>
Most of the mobs there can take items of folks in 3 ways.<br>
<br>
1. Mugging<br>
Durring a fight, a mob can randomly take items of folks it is fighting up to its internal limit of things it can carry. When you kill the mob you do get the items back, of course you have to proove it is yours . . .<br>
<br>
2. Stealthy Robbing.<br>
There are mobs that wander the zone, some are invis, some can morph, they will rob you and sneak away, when caught and killed they do give up the items they steal . . . trackers essential to work out where those steathy robbers are.<br>
<br>
3. Boss mobs<br>
The most heineous of all are the boss mobs, if you get on there shite list (by fighitng or pulling or . . .) you receive the message, you feel another take your place.<br>
<br>
At this point a duplicate of you has been created and every 1 minute removes an item from your bank, this continues until its inventory is full or you leave the zone forcing the shadow to return to the zone. At this time you will see a mob in the zone called say Intra's shadow if it stole from me. If you kill it items will be on it.<br>
<br>
<br>
These are the 3 types of mobs, of course all mobs in the zones steal so . . . imagine the little hatchlings traps that spawn 2-10 little fighitng stealing monsters<br>
<br>
I wonder if anyone would go there :-)<br>
<br>
Imagine an open raid to this hell hole :-)<br>
<br>
*admires herself in the mirror*<br>
*smiles at the nice Teir'Dal face&quot;<br>
<br>
Hugs<br>
<br>
Intra and Sena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 581<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/18/02 4:01:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2164.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Planes of Thievery</span><hr size=1> Too easy to evade the issues...<br>
