<br>
It's already a pain to organize a 30+ person raid by forming groups, funding buffs/ports and making sure its timed where everyone can go. Now you'll have to write down every single item each person has so to know if the person shouting that the item on the corpse is his is telling the truth or not.<br>
<br>
What about loot that drops from the mob that wasn't stolen? All the items on the mob might be stolen items only but then there will be the one mob that had an dropped item. How would you know? Without a written down list of the hundreds of items the whole raid has, someone could say it was theirs and with no others speaking up, everyone will believe him.<br>
<br>
On top of it being a complete pain to raid, every rogue in EQ would be complaining. They can't steal weapons/armor from mobs. So why can they steal ours? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubraellarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Braellarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/22/02 6:22:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2164.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm</span><hr size=1> Imagine a zone where nothing went with you but you could only summon items... hmmm.<br>
